<title>UK: Radamec wins contract from Racal Radar.</title>
<headline>Radamec wins contract from Racal Radar.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-05-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>Britain's Radamec Group Plc said on Friday it had won a contract from Racal Radar Defence Systems, a unit of Racal Elecronics Plc, worth over two million stg.</p>
<p>It said in a statement it would supply stabilised platforms and servo electronics for the &quot;Searchwater 2000&quot; radar systems to be used by the Royal Navy's Sea King airborne early warning MK 7 helicopter programme.</p>
<p>--London Newsroom +44 171 542 4019</p>
